
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000


###
GET / HTTP1.1
Host: {{baseUrl}}
User-Agent: HTTPie/2.4.0
Accept: text/plain


### Request (text/plain)
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: text/plain


### Request (text/html)
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: text/html


### Request (application/json)
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/json

### Request (application/xml)
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: application/xml

###
GET {{baseUrl}}/
Accept: acme/custom-type

### HTML page that references an image
GET {{baseUrl}}/page
Accept: text/html


### Fetch the referenced image directly
GET {{baseUrl}}/images/demo.svg
Accept: image/svg+xml


### Echo: shows what the server received (query + headers + JSON body)
POST {{baseUrl}}/echo?debug=true
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json
X-Custom-Header: hello

{
	"demo": 123,
	"note": "look at headers/query/body"
}


### List items
GET {{baseUrl}}/items
Accept: application/json


### Get one item (existing id)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items/1
Accept: application/json


### Create item (POST)
# @name createItem
POST {{baseUrl}}/items
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
	"name": "Marker",
	"price": 2.75
}


### Capture created item id for later requests
@createdId = {{createItem.response.body.$.id}}


### Get created item (uses id captured from createItem response)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}
Accept: application/json


### Replace item (PUT) — full update
PUT {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
	"name": "Marker (wide)",
	"price": 3.25
}


### Partial update (PATCH) — update one field
PATCH {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}
Content-Type: application/json
Accept: application/json

{
	"price": 3.5
}


### HEAD (same as GET but no body) — check headers
HEAD {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}


### OPTIONS — allowed methods for /items (see Allow header)
OPTIONS {{baseUrl}}/items


### Delete item (DELETE) — returns 204 No Content
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}


### Confirm delete (should be 404)
GET {{baseUrl}}/items/{{createdId}}
Accept: application/json


### Not found route (default 404 handler)
GET {{baseUrl}}/does-not-exist
Accept: application/json

